header.gameNote: FRESNO STATE TOURNAMENT AT FRESNO CA

article.headline: South Alabama 76, Winston-Salem 58
article.story: FRESNO, Calif. (AP) -- Daon Merritt scored 18 points and Demetric Bennett added 17, leading South Alabama to a 76-58 victory over Winton-Salem State on Sunday. Brandon Davis added 10 points and a game-high 11 rebounds for South Alabama (2-1), helping the Jaguars to a 39-27 advantage on the boards. Darrell Wonge scored 15 points for Winton-Salem State (0-3), who are in their first season at Division I. Stephen Cowherd and Bennett both made 3-pointers in the opening minutes as South Alabama bolted to a 16-4 lead. After the Rams fought back to tie the game at 27-27, the Jaguars closed the first half with seven straight points. South Alabama put the game away with a 13-0 scoring run midway through the second half. Bennett finished 4-for-5 from three-point range. Merritt went 3-for-5.
